###
### --- Delivery Personnel API ---
###

### Create a new delivery person
POST http://localhost:3000/api/delivery
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Mike Wheeler",
  "phone": "555-8888",
  "vehicle_id": "KA-01-MJ-1983"
}


### Update a delivery person's status and location (e.g., driver with ID 1)
# This simulates the driver's app sending a location update when they come online.
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/delivery/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "available",
  "latitude": 12.9716,
  "longitude": 77.5946
}

###
### --- Delivery Assignment API ---
###

### Assign the closest available driver to an order (e.g., order with ID 1)
# NOTE: Before running, make sure you have a delivery person with status 'available'
# and an order that has not yet been assigned.
POST http://localhost:3000/api/orders/1/assign-delivery
